==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Untented
<hw>Un*tent"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets> not +
<ets>tent</ets> a covering.]</ety> <def>Having no tent or tents, as a
soldier or a field.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untented</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Untented
<hw>Un*tent"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref. <ets>un-</ets> not +
<ets>tented</ets>, p. p. of <ets>tent</ets> to probe.]</ety> <def>Not
tended; not dressed. See 4th <er>Tent</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>untented</qex> woundings of a father's curse⟦br⟧
Pierce every sense about thee!</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unthank</ent>⟦br⟧
